<br>
As for some other rules the one they need to work on is the ninja looting problem on the server. They say the problem is they have to catch the ninja by some confusing ridiculous set of rules. <br>
<br>
Heres an idea seance most of the major ninja looting seems to be things like Crown and heads off mobs King Tormax. Change the code so it shows who loots what in the chat screens of not just the group by in a small area around the corpse.<br>
<br>
If that does not work they could always change the code so for 15 minutes only the group that killed the mob and the people they /loot &lt;Persons name&gt; &lt;corpse name&gt;. That way theres a safe 15 minute window to give out loot and not worry about ninja looters.<br>
<br>
What do you guys think about the idea of a loot consent command with 15 minute window for mobs with corpses that last 45 minutes?<br>
<br>
Rniria the pissed off cleric. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhorendusofstc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HorendusOfSTC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(7/2/02 6:02:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernrantsandflames.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2770.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: GMs and the Everchanging Ruleset</span><hr size=1> I wouldnt mind seeing a /lootconsent  implimented. I think that would be nice, now the 15 minutes of safetime, thats a little different. Sounds like a decent idea but could there eventually be conflict with that? I do not see any right off, but there could possibly be some there.<br>
