<br>
We killed King Tormax.  I was on the corpse immediately, my loot timer wore off.  As I went back down, someone was already on it.  I asked the other officer -- they weren't.  By the time another officer got on the corpse, the crown and head had been taken.  We all know that faction leeches are always present... with consent or without.  There isn't too much to be done about it.  And we figured.. well, shit, this sucks... let's petition and get the stuff back.<br>
<br>
The guide told Quixen he'd escalate the petition to a GM.  Nearly 3 hours later....  The GM tells Quixen that he needs specific names or our claim of ninja looting can't be resolved.  At this point, I'm wondering if the GM understands what &quot;ninja&quot; is.  We didn't have a name.. we have a /who on the zone... but there were 145 people there.  The GM will only accept one name.  We did some quick talking and game him one name.<br>
<br>
He claimed to check the players inventory and tell us that the items weren't looted by that player and logs off the server.  ????  Multiple petitions and complaints go through.. some GMs saying they can check loot logs, some not.  Some saying that a level 1 ogre (sorry, Flippett) might have had it, but deleted -- which was not true.<br>
<br>
In the end, an email was sent to the head of customer service at Verant.  Nothing more has been said or done on their part.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure how to proceed.  Buyer beware applies here as well, I suppose.  Ninja looters can and will get away with stuff... simply because Verant employees can and will do nothing.  The inconsistency with how they treat players and incidences is truly sad.  You'd think in such an organization, there would be some kind of ruleset for common occurences.  Well, if there is, they forgot to hand out the copies. <p><p>
